comments.text:
+No no  I understand the point you are trying to make, but honestly I think 
it's kind of ridiculous you have a problem with him behaving 
"stereotypically." Yes, maybe that might cause some people who are...A bit 
less well versed with gays to think it's what a gay is like. But I for one 
(usually) have enough faith in people to think they'll realize that 
applying any one concept to an entire group is stupid. I have a lot of 
problems with people criticizing people for being too "typical," it's 
something that seems to happen most with gender roles and sexuality. The 
point about true acceptance is letting everyone be who they want to be, 
regardless of their preferences in life. Tyler is a loud, colorful, 
extroverted kind of guy. I for one think he'd be pretty similar even if by 
some twist of fate he had ended up straight. Anyway, I think the point is 
that he's not going to stop being a gay icon, and he's not going to change 
and become...Less himself. And I'm sorry that you want more representation 
for the kind of gay that IS often underrepresented by the media, I think 
having "icons" from all walks would be pretty great. But there's no reason 
at all to tear down Tyler, or any "stereotypical" person for just being who 
they are. If you want someone to get more recognition, work for that, for 
promoting them. Not dissing someone else. Because for someone to be 
successful they don't have to crush someone else. Everyone should just try 
to get along. Everyone. <3 :)

captions.text:
- Why, hello, everyone,
my name is Tyler Oakley,
and y'all always have so many questions,
and I always have so many answers,
which means it is time for another
Q and Slay.

Now, I normally do Q and
Slays by asking you guys

to submit questions on
Twitter, but today I was like,
"You know what?
"We just got done with a full month
"of collaborations with YouTubers,
"I wanna collaborate with you guys."

So, I asked you to submit
questions to me on Skype.

You had to add me and then send
me a video of your question,

and I'm really excited
to see you guys' videos

because I'm like, "This
is finally a chance for me

"to put some faces to
some of your user names,

"and get to know you guys
a little bit better."
So, let's hear what you guys had to ask.

- Hey, Tyler, my question
for the Q and Slay is that
when is Troye going to meet Queen Jackie?

Because you've met up
the (mumbling) family,

so we wanted Troye to meet
Jackie, and get a selfie.
- Oh, this is a good question.

So, yeah, as you guys know
I have gone to Australia
to meet Troye's family.
You know, the times are uh...
They're coming, is all I'll say.
I don't know exactly when,

but we have plans for him to
come to Michigan in the future.
I know you guys hate the word "soon,"
so I'm not gonna say, "It's soon,"
but in the near future. (laughs)

- My question is out of
all of your August videos,
which one was the most fun to make?

Which one was the most
mentally scarring to make?
And which one was the most messy to make?
- The messiest had to be by far

the one I did with
SUPERFRUIT, Scott and Mitch,

where we (laughs) had to put
our hands behind our backs
and eat a whole bunch of spaghetti.
And then the funnest might have been
the one I did with Connor.
Him and I just have always so much fun,
and so we did a whispering challenge

where we whispered pickup
lines to each other,
and we were just laughing the whole time.
Also, the one with Zoe,
we just always have fun making videos.
And then the most mentally scarring
would have to be the one I made with Dan.
(laughs) It was like...
We had to watch just the weirdest stuff.
This month was so fun,

there were a couple
that put me through it.

- My question for you is
what is the smelliest thing
you have ever smelled in your entire life?
- Okay, so this is (laughs)...
This question is really asking me a lot.

But, the smelliest thing
that I've ever smelled
would have to be...
(laughs) I don't know.

I've smelled some things
in my times, girl,

you don't even know where
my nose has been. (laughs)
I'm not gonna answer that.
You guys can...
I mean, I'm sure you can come up

with something even
stinkier for me to smell
in a fan-fiction, so you go hog-wild.

- Hi, Tyler, my name is Benji,
and my question for you is

besides Darren Criss, who is
your next celebrity crush?
- Hey, Benji!
Well, I have a couple celebrity crushes.
I'm very thirsty.

If you don't know that
about me, learn it now,
because it is overwhelming
and my thirst needs to be quenched.
I love Zac Efron, I love Nick Jonas,

(sighs) Big Sean, I just
have a lot of thirst,
and nothing seems to be quenching it.

So, if y'all know any of
those boys, hook a brother up.
- [All girls] Hi, Tyler.
- So, we have a question for your
- [All girls] Q and Slay.
- So, our question is

if you had a movie
written about your life,
who would play who?
We love you.
- [All girls] Bye.

- Hey, ladies, (laughs) I
feel like this is so fun

that I finally get to
see your guys' faces.
But, if I had a movie about myself,
I would be played by none other obviously
than Ellen DeGeneres.

And then my mother, it
would have to be somebody

with like expertise acting
skills, just the right look,

and that would obviously
have to be none other than
Miranda Sings.
- Okay, so my question for you

is what is the weirdest
collab you've ever done?

- Okay, so I have done
millions and millions
of collabs, obviously.
I am the Collaboration Queen,
but my favorite weirdest that got me

most out of my own box
collab that I've ever done
would have to be something that I did
when I had only 4,000 subscribers,
and this was a few years ago,
and it was none other than Grace Helbig.
We did a video on her channel
where I had to kind of do a skit,
and as you guys know, I don't do skits.
So, it was kind of weird for me to do,
but it came out really cute
and the looking back now,

considering all the things
that she's accomplishing

and all the things that
we have done together,
me and my people,
it's just crazy to look back at us
when we were just like baby YouTubers
collaborating together.

- How do you get your favorite
YouTuber to notice you?
Because I don't have any luck,
except for when you favorited my tweet,
thanks by the way.
- Girl, it is easy to be noticed by me!
I feel like I am like on the internet
all day long every day.

So, all you gotta do is
maintain your regular level
of fine, fresh, fierce fabulousness,

and keep slaying the game,
and I'll see everything.
- Hi Queen Tyler, my name is Kaitlyn,

and my question for you if you
got offered your own TV show,
would you give up YouTube to do it?
- Now this is really interesting,

because I actually have
gotten a few offers like this.
Even back after I graduated college,

I was applying for jobs
and they were all saying,

"If you get this job,
would you quit YouTube?"
It's just the hardest thing,

and it's probably why
I didn't get any real

aspirational jobs that
I wanted out of college,
was because I said, "No."
Because I feel like to be my best self

in another environment, whether
it's a job or a TV show,

I still have to maintain who
I am outside of that career.

And that is very much
me being the YouTuber,
and so for people to not get that,

they don't get me, and they
don't deserve to work with me.
- If you weren't a famous YouTuber,
what would you be doing instead?
- So, if I weren't a YouTuber,
I would probably be a model. (laughs)

I sometimes get to do these
like fun little photo shoots
and I feel ridiculous in every way,

because I'm like smizing
and like giving angles,

and like working every
single fib of the camera.
But, I am not cut out for it,
but I would love to try (laughs).

Like I said, I get the
opportunity sometimes
when photographers want to do something.

I once did a little
photo shoot that I did.
I think like a month ago,

and I have a whole bunch
of fun pictures from it
that I am not gonna post all over Twitter

and Tumblr and everywhere,
because that's a bit much.

I've been showing you guys
a few of the pictures,
but if you wanna see some more of them,

I will put them in a little
folder that you can download.
All you gotta do is click the link below
to my OneDrive account.

It's got some exclusive
pictures, if you wanna get those.
The link to that is below.
But that is all I have for you guys today.
If you like this Q and Slay,
be sure to give it a thumbs up,

and I might do more Q
and Slays just like this.
But yeah, thank you so much
for all of your support this week.
I have had tons of fun little projects,
as you guys know, from my last video.
My Slumber Party Tour is kickin' off.

If you wanna get tickets to
that, the links are below.
It'll say if there's still tickets left,
but there may be, there might not be.
Click below, you will see.
And then, my podcast has been such a hit.
You guys have been giving it so much love.

If you haven't checked
out the first episode,
the link to that is below.

Subscribe on iTunes,
it is completely free.
A lot of y'all are like, "You know what?
"I don't money, Tyler.

"I don't got the budget
for some of these things."

This is free, so this is
a gift just for you guys.
It'll be free every single week,
so be sure to subscribe to that on iTunes.

And hopefully you guys
continue to love it.

But that is all, I hope you
guys have a fabulous life,
and until next time, later.
(upbeat island music)

title: Regarding Me Quitting YouTube (#AskTyler #27) | Tyler Oakley
